{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_6_83','text':"Mobile Banking users in Nepal has been drastically increased every year due to financial awareness to the general people as well as enhancement of retail base in the banking industry. With various initiatives from government as well as private level for enhancing access to finance, the retail base of the banks has been encouragingly expanded. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_18_32','text':"Income Levels (NPR Lakh) ;Customer Segment ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_18_34','text':"2–10 ;Mass Market ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_18_36','text':"10–50 ;Mass Affluent ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_18_38','text':"50–400 ;Super Affluent ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_18_40','text':"400–4,000 ;HNW ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_18_42','text':"4000–120,000 ;Super HNW ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_18_44','text':"Above 120,000 ;Ultra HNW ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_18_45','text':"HNW – High Net Worth ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_18_48','text':"( ;Source;-,;-,;-… ;Celent Research) ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_18_49','text':"If we look at the customer segments above, the first three segments namely Mass Market, Mass Affluent and Super Affluent are the most important segments for banks with regard to their retail banking initiatives. The products and services will be structured mostly to meet the requirements of the above segments. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_18_50','text':"The fundamental assumptions about customers for building retail banking products and services are briefly explained as follows;-,;-,;-… ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_18_51','text':"Customers are different. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_18_52','text':"Needs of the customers are different. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_18_53','text':"Each customer will have different sets of need for financial services. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_18_54','text':"The requirements of customers for financial services will be unique. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_18_55','text':"Customers can be broadly grouped together based on their need pyramids. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_18_56','text':"Customers can be grouped together based on their income, age, geography, profession, employment, vocation gender and family size. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_18_57','text':"Product and services can be developed for a single or a combination of the above elements to satisfy most of the needs. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_18_58','text':"Products and services can be structured on a niche basis within one or any of the above elements. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_18_59','text':"The above assumptions about customers help banks to develop suitable products and services to cater to the need spectrum of the customers. To understand this concept, a look into the ‘Maslow’s Hierarchy of needs’ theory is appropriate. The theory will help us to understand how banks structure products to match the different stages of the need pyramid of the customers. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_18_60','text':"Customers buy the products and services of the bank primarily to satisfy their needs and if their needs and banks’ products match, there is absolute synchrony and if the benefits promised by the bank to the customer are delivered then there will be absolute satisfaction from the customer end. The requirements of the customers in general can be related with the need hierarchy theory by Abraham Maslow. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_19_9','text':"S. No. ;Need Level ;Matching Banking, Investment and Insurance Products ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_19_12','text':"1. ;Physiological Needs ;Core Savings Accounts ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_19_13','text':"Personal Accident Cover ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_19_14','text':"Housing Loans ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_19_17','text':"2. ;Security/Safety Needs ;Recurring, Fixed Deposit Products. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_19_18','text':"Life Insurance Products – Endowment Products with low premium, long tenor and high maturity amounts. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_19_19','text':"Tax Planning Banking, Insurance and Mutual Fund Products. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_19_22','text':"3. ;Social Needs ;Consumer Loans ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_19_23','text':"Personal Loans ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_19_24','text':"Home Loans ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_19_25','text':"Car Loans ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_19_26','text':"Loans for Professional Developments for Doctors, Engineers, Lawyers, etc. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_19_29','text':"4. ;Esteem Needs ;Special Term Deposit Products. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_19_30','text':"Term Insurance Products. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_19_31','text':"Second Housing Loans/Home Improvement/Home Décor Loans. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_19_34','text':"5. ;Self Actualization Needs ;Pensioners Loans ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_19_35','text':"Retirement Solutions in Banking & Pension Plans in insurance ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_19_36','text':"Senior Citizens Term Deposit Products ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_19_37','text':"The above table is only suggestive and not absolute and products may tend to overlap across the need spectrum and again the banks may come across all the stages run concurrently for the customer base and hence there is tremendous opportunity for banks to convert the potential available across needs for their huge customer base. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_35_14','text':"In the highly competitive field of banking, almost all banks offer products with the features of the product being almost the same. But then how the bank marketer will have an edge over other competitors? For achieving, this marketer has to adopt product differentiation. The efforts of the marketer should be to differentiate his product as far as possible from the competitor’s product. The differentiation strategies are adopted by differentiating their features, benefits and satisfaction level by doing some value addition to the product. For achieving this, a tool available for bank marketers is to highlight the US. P. of the product."}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_35_16','text':"Like this, Interest is payable monthly instead of quarterly by many banks in Nepal is also a type of US. P.. Earlier almost 20 years back in Nepal, Interest on all the savings account used to be calculated on monthly minimum balance and few banks, at starting, launched their product with the provision of interest calculation on daily balance basis. It was a truly a great US. P. of that product in those days."}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_42_5','text':"Are the numbers of enquiries very high? Have you applied for additional credit lines, recently? Unnecessary and frequent shopping for credit or too many new accounts can be taken as an indicator of being over- hungry for loans and impact the score negatively."}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_44_1','text':"warning signs in credit score"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_44_2','text':"The behavioural pattern of the borrowers will impact the credit score of the borrowers. The following are some of the signals."}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_48_13','text':"The credit score is calculated based on the individual’s credit behaviour in very recent years. So, does that mean the person can present himself as a worthy borrower to a potential lender despite having slipped on debt repayments a long time ago? Not really."}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_14','text':"Purpose of Loan ;Part financing of;-,;-,;-… ;Purchase of Land for residential purchase ;Refinancing of house constructed within 6 months ;Outright purchase of house (fully or partially constructed) ;Construction of house on the land already owned ;Repair or renovation of the house ;Purchase of house/apartment developed by the housing development companies ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_16','text':"Tenure ;i) Maximum 30 year inclusive of moratorium of max. 12 months ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_17','text':"ii) Maximum 10 years in case of repair and renovation including moratorium ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_19','text':"Eligibility Criteria ;i) Salaried Employees ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_20','text':"ii) Self Employed professionals like doctors, engineers, Lawyers etc. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_22','text':"iii) Other individuals who have identified source of income like lease, pension etc. ;(If any person from the same family is sponsoring the home loan his/her income can be considered but personal guarantee of the sponsor should be obtained.) ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_24','text':"Other Criteria ;i) Minimum age of the applicant should be minimum 18 years and maximum age should not exceed 65 year however the applicant can’t be more than 70 years till the entire loan gets repaid. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_25','text':"ii) E. M. I. should not exceed 50% of monthly uncommitted total income of the applicant and the sponsors. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_26','text':"iii) The house being financed should be within municipal area and if it’s not municipal area there should be branch office of the bank. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_27','text':"iv) If the financing is for purchase of land only, there should be commitment to start construction on thus purchased land within 12 months. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_28','text':"v) The loan should be secured by registered mortgage of the property being financed by the bank. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_29','text':"vi) Refinancing may be allowed but the purchase should not be more than 12 months older. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_31','text':"Loan Amount ;Minimum amount of the loan should be Rupees 5 lacs and maximum 200 lacs ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_32','text':"Maximum amount must not exceed 90% of the cost of construction of building certified by the Bank’s authorized valuator in case of financing of building construction. The security coverage, however, should be at least 70% of F.  M.  V.  of the property for first time home buyer. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_33','text':"In case of outright purchase of land or land and building, the loan amount should not exceed the value mentioned in title transfer deed of the property. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_35','text':"Maximum 90% of the estimated cost certified by the Bank’s authorized valuator in case of repair and renovation of house. ;(Estimated cost of the property should be certified by Architect/ Engineer/ Developer/ Authorized valuator of the Bank) ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_37','text':"Pricing Structure ;Interest rate will be base rate plus premium on the basis of risk rating score and charges, fees and commission on the facility should be as per the standard tariff and charges published by the bank from time to time. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_39','text':"Disbursement Modality ;Disbursement to be made upon completion of loan documents. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_40','text':"1. For construction of building on prior acquired land / repair and renovation of house ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_41','text':"For construction of building on prior acquired/possessed land / repair and renovation of house, the loan amount will be disbursed on advance/reimbursement basis in instalments depending on the progress of construction after confirming that the applicant has invested his/her pro-rata share towards the required margin amount. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_42','text':"Drawdown may be allowed in tranches including mobilization advance being within the limit prescribed by regulator in terms of L.  T.  V.  as well as the drawing power on the basis of progress report submitted by the valuator engineer and the F.  M.  V.  of the present construction. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_43','text':"Disbursement of instalments shall be based on the progress of construction. Before each drawdown, the Bank’s authorized valuator should certify progress of the construction and equity contribution from the borrower. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_44','text':"10% of the approved loan amount should be released as the last instalment after submission of building construction completion certificate, final valuation report and comprehensive insurance policy of the building. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_45','text':"Total amount of loan should be disbursed within 12 (twelve) months from the date of first disbursement of the loan. If total disbursement cannot take place within this period, further 6 (six) months may be allowed for drawing the balance amount on case to case basis. However, repayment should be as per the originally approved repayment schedule. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_46','text':"2. For outright purchase of property ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_47','text':"In case of outright purchase of property, the total sanctioned loan amount will be disbursed in full value in the borrower’s account which shall be transferred to the existing owner (seller) by crediting his/her/their account or in form of account payee cheque/draft/manager’s cheque drawn in his/her/their favor after completion of required loan documents. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_50','text':"3. For outright purchase of building or property developed by the real estate developers ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_51','text':"In such case the total sanctioned loan amount will be disbursed in full value to the real estate developer by crediting their account or in form of account payee cheque/draft/manager’s cheque drawn in their favor at the time of registration after confirming that the applicant has paid for his/her contribution amount and completion of required loan documents. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_53','text':"In case of financing of under-construction building, 10% of loan amount shall not be released till the submission of building construction completion certificate. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_54','text':"4. For purchase of land for residential purpose ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_55','text':"Total sanctioned loan amount will be disbursed in full value based on the valuation as certified by the Bank’s approved valuator. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_56','text':"Registered mortgage over the property must be executed prior to disbursement of loan. In exceptional cases if registered mortgage over the property cannot be executed before disbursal of the loan, it should be completed within maximum 3 (three) working days from the date of disbursal of the loan. But if the disbursement is to be done before registered mortgage all other security documentation must be completed before disbursement except mortgage. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_57','text':"5. For re-finance of Housing Loan of other Banks / FI (Takeover) ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_58','text':"The applicant must submit the concerned bank’s letter ‘stating that the loan falls under “Pass” category as per N.  R.  B.  directives. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_59','text':"The applicant must also submit loan statement for verification of timely settlement of installment and other dues prior processing of loan application. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_60','text':"6. For re-finance of house constructed within 12 months ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_61','text':"Building should be recently constructed (already obtained building construction completion certificate but within 12 months) or under construction stage. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_62','text':"Disbursement shall be based on value determined by the authorized valuator. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_63','text':"In case of financing of under-construction building, 10% of loan amount shall not be released till the submission of building construction submission certificate ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_65','text':"Repayment ;A moratorium period of maximum 12 (twelve) months may be provided from the date of first drawdown. Interest will be charged during the period on quarterly basis. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_66','text':"E. M. I. over a period of 25 years at maximum, and 10 years at maximum, in case of loan for repair and renovation of house. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_67','text':"Principal repayment to be commenced from the application day falling immediately after the moratorium period. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_69','text':"Prepayment ;Prepayment of the loan shall be allowed under following conditions;-,;-,;-… ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_70','text':"Any amount in multiple of Rupees 1 lacs except in case of final settlement of the loan in full. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_71','text':"The amount prepaid shall not be redrawn under any circumstance. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_73','text':"Prepayment fee shall be applied as per the Standard Tariff of Charges of the Bank but N.  R.  B.  directive should be followed in application of prepayment such as;-,;-,;-… ;o Prepayment fee may be recovered by the bank upto 20% of the initial loan processing fee. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_74','text':"o If the loan is to be taken over by another bank swap fee may be recovered in the same pattern as mentioned in above. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_75','text':"Upon prepayment, E. M. I. schedule may be re-aligned after obtaining approval of authorized C. A.D holder. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_77','text':"Security ;Land or land and building being financed with motorable access ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_78','text':"Apartments developed by real estate developers ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_79','text':"Personal Guarantees as applicable ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_81','text':"Documentation ;Basic Documentation;-,;-,;-… ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_82','text':"Loan Application to be completed by the applicant. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_83','text':"Location map of the applicant’s/ guarantor’s residence and proposed collateral. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_84','text':"Photograph and copy of citizenship certificate of the applicant /sponsor/ guarantor ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_85','text':"Net worth statement of the applicant/guarantor/sponsor, as applicable. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_86','text':"Title Transfer Deed (Rajinama, Bakaspatra, etc.), where applicable. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_87','text':"o Primary documents related to the property being financed viz. (i) title deed, (ii) four boundary certificate, (iii) trace map, (iv) drawings of building to be constructed, (v) building construction permission letter from competent authority, (vi) latest revenue receipt of land or land and building offered as security. (vii) In case of loan secured against building within a municipality, documents certifying fulfillment of required standards set by the competent authority such as approved drawing (Naksapass), approval from concerned authorities and building construction completion certificate. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_88','text':"PAN certificate in the name of borrower ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_89','text':"Self-declaration of the borrower with respect to purchase of land for residential purpose (in case of loan for purchase of land only). ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_90','text':"Income statement or cash flow of the applicant or sponsors;-,;-,;-… following proof for substantiation of the income or cash flow should be submitted;-,;-,;-… ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_91','text':"a) In case of salaried individuals;-,;-,;-… (i) Certification of salary or salary statement from the employer. (ii) Bank account statements, as applicable. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_92','text':"b) In case of self-employed professionals;-,;-,;-… (i) Registration document from concerned professional association/ council, (ii) Details of income, (iii) Bank account statements, as applicable. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_93','text':"c) In case of self-employed businessman;-,;-,;-… (i) Business Registration Document, (ii) Income Tax Certificate, (iii) Self-declared financial statements in case of individual/ proprietorship/ partnership firm or latest Audited Financial Statements in case of Limited Company, (iv) Bank account statements, as applicable. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_94','text':"d) In case of other sources;-,;-,;-… (i) Latest lease payment receipt or agreements, (ii) title deed of property, as applicable, (iii) Details of other lease income. If such lease is generated from the asset that is financed by loan from other Bank or financial institution, only residual income net of installment due should be considered in the evaluation, (iv) Pension slip, (v) interest received statement etc., ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_95','text':"e) Remittance income;-,;-,;-… (i) Remittance receipt (at least three), (ii) account statement evidencing the receipt of remittance in bank’s account, (iii) account statement of income generating person. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_96','text':"Loan Documentation;-,;-,;-… ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_97','text':"Offer Letter;-,;-,;-… Accepted copy of sanction letter (Offer Letter) of the Bank. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_98','text':"Security Documents ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_99','text':"1. Registered Mortgage Deed over Land/Land and Building/apartments, as applicable. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_100','text':"2. Cross-collateral deed, as applicable ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_101','text':"3. Re-mortgage deed, as applicable ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_102','text':"4. Internal Loan Deed. ;"}]},
