{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_105','text':"Other Documents ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_106','text':"1. Valuation report of the property offered as collateral. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_107','text':"2. Original copy of Insurance Policy endorsed in favour of the Bank and insurance premium paid receipt. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_108','text':"The applicant shall ensure that the building forming part of the security for the facility is insured at all times. A comprehensive insurance policy (covering at least against the risk of fire and earthquake) with the Bank’s interest noted on it should be submitted as an evidence for the same. If our loan is extended for financing furnishing, then the furniture should also be insured against risk of burglary. The borrower should submit the insurance policy or policies to the Bank prior disbursement of the loan. Renewals of the policy or policies should be made within its validity. If the borrower fails to renew the policy on time, the Bank may intervene and renew it with the existing insurer or insure it with any other insurer debiting customer’s account or booking loan as applicable. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_109','text':"Insurance of the building under constructions to be done as per progress report certified by the Bank’s authorized valuator under- “Building under Construction Clause” or as specified by insurance company. The applicant shall pay all incidental (legal and contingency) expenditures related to the insurance or process ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_111','text':"Recovery Process ;1. Forthcoming dues (E.  M.  I. /EPI etc.) to be advised to the customer one week before the due date in advance. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_112','text':"2. A follow up to be made after 15 days of due date if not paid. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_113','text':"3. Constant follow up to be made in case of delinquency in an account > 1 month. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_114','text':"4. In case of delinquency in an account >3 months, a reminder letter allowing the borrower 35 days to clear the overdue amount would be sent. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_115','text':"5. CSR (Credit Strategy Review) regarding recovery action to be raised in case of all non-performing loans and approval to be obtained from the C. A.D holder. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_117','text':"Other terms and Conditions ;Based on the Product Paper, the Bank may enter into any agreement with real estate developers, administer and execute the loans on a mass scale. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_118','text':"Each account need not be reviewed annually. However, in case of delinquency in an account for >3 consecutive months, Credit Strategy Report (CSR) regarding recovery action needs to be placed in each folder. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_119','text':"Charge over the property should be released to the applicant upon full repayment of the dues (principal + interest) but third party transfers are prohibited. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_120','text':"Security in the name of third party is prohibited under this product facility. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_122','text':"Service Procedure ;Submission of duly filled application along with the required supporting documents ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_123','text':"Personal interview by the Bank official. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_124','text':"Conducting collateral assets site visit, physical verification of repayment source, where required. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_125','text':"Processing and submission of credit proposal for approval. The proposal to accompany and fulfil all relevant terms and conditions. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_126','text':"After approval of loan, the Bank issues an offer letter to the applicant ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_127','text':"Upon receiving confirmation to the offer letter from applicant, the Bank to initiate valuation of proposed property through Bank’s approved valuator and security documentation process ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_128','text':"The applicant after adding his confirmation to the offer letter pays applicable fees ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_129','text':"Mortgage over property being part of the collateral. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_130','text':"Disbursement is made after confirming the applicant has invested his part of contribution and having obtained processing fee. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_131','text':"Undertaking monitoring and control functions, as appropriate. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_133','text':"Service Standard ;Each application should be processed within 3 (three) working days from the date of receipt of all necessary documents. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_146','text':"Eligibility ;Salaried employees, Professionals, Self-employed persons. Requests are also considered from NRIs, PIOs, HUF, Proprietorship Firms, Partnership firms, and corporate for their employees/quarte ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_148','text':"Purpose ;To purchase/construct house/flat. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_149','text':"To renovate/extend/repair existing house/flat. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_150','text':"To purchase a plot of land for construction of house. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_151','text':"To acquire household articles along with the house/flat – for furnishing the house/flat. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_153','text':"Quantum of Loan ;For construction/purchase of a house/flat – No upper ceiling in many banks Repairs/renovation/extension to house/flat – amount varies from bank to bank Purchase of a plot – amount varies from bank to bank ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_154','text':"Purchase/acquire household articles for furnishing the house/flat – amount varies from bank to bank ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_156','text':"Eligible Quantum of Loan/E. M. I. ;Calculation of quantum of loan is The method of reckoning eligible related to Income/repayment capacity finance varies from bank to bank. of proponent/borrower. However, repayment capacity needs ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_158','text':"Salaried Employees;-,;-,;-… ;to be ensured from the existing source of income ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_159','text':"Self-employed/ Eligible finance is calculated by banks ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_160','text':"Professionals etc.;-,;-,;-… based on I-T Returns ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_162','text':"HUF/Proprietorship/Partnership Eligible finance is calculated by banks Firm/Company;-,;-,;-… ;based on cash accruals ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_163','text':"In case of Individuals;-,;-,;-… ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_164','text':"Net take home pay/income (net of all deductions including E. M. I. of Proposed loan) should not be generally less than 40% of the gross monthly salary/income of applicants. But for high income applicants, lesser take home pay even up to 15% of gross income is being considered by some banks. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_165','text':"Margin (For 1st House) Amount Margin (%) ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_166','text':"Upto 30 Lakh 10 ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_167','text':"NPR 30 Lakh and up to Nepali Rupees 75 Lakh 20 ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_168','text':"NPR 75 Lakh 25 ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_171','text':"Margin is subject to RBI stipulated L.  T.  V.  (Loan to Value) of Max. 90% for loans upto 30.00 Lakh, Max. 80% for loans above Nepali Rupees ;30.00 Lakh & upto Nepali Rupees 75 Lakh, and Max. 75% for loans above 75 Lakh. ;Banks should not include stamp duty, registration and other documentation charges in the cost of the housing property they finance so that the effectiveness of L.  T.  V.  norms is not diluted. However, in cases where the cost of the house/dwelling units does not exceed 10 lakh, bank may add stamp duty, registration and other documentation charges to the cost of the house/dwelling unit for the purpose of calculating L.  T.  V.  ratio. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_173','text':"Interest (Floating R. O. I. – linked bank’s base rate p.a. at monthly rests) ;R. O. I. varies from bank to bank. RBI has left R. O. I. to the discretion of individual banks ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_175','text':"Processing charges/other expenses ;Processing charges vary from bank to bank. Some banks do not levy any processing charges and some do. The schedule is left at the discretion of individual banks. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_178','text':"Security ;Mortgage/Equitable Mortgage on land/flat/house. ;(if mortgage could not be created at the time of disbursement, banks may get the loan secured by creating charge on alternative assets/ obtaining third party guarantee). ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_181','text':"Disbursement ;Upfront disbursement in case of ready flat/house ;Closely linked to the stages of construction of the housing project/ houses; and Upfront disbursal should not be made in cases of incomplete/under construction/green field housing projects. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_184','text':"Repayment (can be customized) ;Highly flexible – maximum 30 years including moratorium period is considered by banks. Maximum moratorium period of 18 months in case of construction and 3 months in case of purchase is allowed generally by banks. ;Loan to be normally repaid before date of retirement in case of salaried persons and before attaining 65 years of age in case of others. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_186','text':"Special features ;Some banks stipulate health/life insurance of the borrowers as additional terms and conditions. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_193','text':"Other features ;Interest on Daily Reducing Balance Basis ;No Pre-Payment Charges on Floating Rate Loan ;Repayment allowed up to age of 70 years in select cases ;Facility for step up/step down E.  M.  I. s available ;Inclusion of Income of Close relatives for enhanced loan ;Tax Benefit on Interest and Installments repaid in Home Loans ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_194','text':"To have differentiation in housing loan products, many banks add some features to the generic products. For example, the provisional sanction of Home Loan limits to the customers before finalization of the property which enables them to negotiate with the Builder/Seller confidently. Cash credit facilities are also provided by some banks to make the product more attractive. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_195','text':"The property should be valued by the bank’s approved valuer. Newspapers and journals have a data bank that carries price data on properties in different areas of most cities. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_196','text':"The title of the borrower to the property offered as security should be verified by the bank’s lawyer who will go through the chain of title for a stipulated period as per the policies of individual banks. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_197','text':"No loan should be given in respect of those properties which fall in the category of unauthorized colonies unless and until they have been regularized and development and other charges paid. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_51_198','text':"No loan should also be given in respect of properties meant for residential use but which the applicant intends to use for commercial purposes and declares so while applying for loan. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_52_11','text':"Type of Loan ;Hire Purchase Loan (Medium Term Loan in Nature) ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_52_14','text':"Purpose of Loan ;To finance and re-finance private vehicles to be used for personal use only. ;Commercial Vehicles for commercial use. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_52_16','text':"Tenure ;Maximum 10 years for private vehicles and maximum 5 years for commercial vehicles ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_52_25','text':"Eligibility Criteria ;For Private Vehicles ;Self-employed Professionals ;Salaried Employees. ;Individuals with identified income source for example: lease, business, pension etc. ;For Commercial Vehicles ;Experience in Commercial Transport Sector ;Business plan and projection ;Financial and cash flow projections showing enough DSC.  R.  and related licenses and route permit for operation. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_52_28','text':"Other Criteria ;1. Minimum age of the applicant to be 18 Years. ;2 Maximum age of the applicant should not exceed 65 years. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_52_31','text':"Loan Amount ;Minimum 5 lac to maximum 200 lacs depending upon the value of vehicle and repayment capacity of the ;borrower ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_52_33','text':"Margin ;Minimum 20% of the cost of vehicle which ranges from bank to bank and brand to brand of the vehicle. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_52_36','text':"Pricing Structure ;Interest rate, charges, fees and commission on the facility will be as per published standard tariff charges. ;If there is subvention of price by the seller the price will be adjusted accordingly. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_52_40','text':"Disbursement Modality ;Disbursal not to exceed approved financing percentage or loan limit whichever is lower. ;Disbursement to be made upon completion of loan documents. ;Disbursement will be directly made to the supplier/seller of the vehicle ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_52_42','text':"Repayment ;Repayment is done on E. M. I. basis for private auto loans whereas it may be done on EPI basis also by banks for repayment of Commercial auto loans. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_52_48','text':"Prepayment ;Prepayments of the loan shall be allowed under following conditions;-,;-,;-… ;Minimum of Nepali Rupees 50,000/- except in case of final settlement of loan in full. ;The amount prepaid shall be adjusted against the loan limit thus cannot be re-availed. ;Commitment Fee shall be applied as per the Standard Tariff of Charges of the Bank. ;N.  R.  B.  directives may be applicable in prepayment where Banks are not allowed to recover any prepayment fees from the borrowers ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_52_54','text':"Security ;Registration of vehicle being financed. ;Land or land & building with motorable access (as applicable). ;Lien over cash or near cash security (as applicable). ;Comprehensive insurance covering major risk of loss of full value of the vehicle ;Any other security (as applicable) ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_52_61','text':"Documentation ;Loan Application to be completed by the applicant ;Pro-forma invoice from the dealer/seller of the vehicle addressed in the name of the applicant stating the details of the vehicle (model, options etc.) and quoted price (in case of new vehicle). ;Valuation report from the authorized vehicle dealer of particular vehicle /assessor of the Bank showing details of the vehicle (in case of refinancing) ;Photograph and copy of citizenship of the applicant/ sponsor/Guarantor ;Map of the applicant’s/sponsor’s/guarantor’s residence. ;Net worth statement of applicant/sponsor/guarantor, as applicable. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_52_64','text':"Income statement or cash flow details of the applicant/ sponsor/ guarantor/ business entity-proof for substantiation of the income to be submitted. Whereas for commercial auto loans all the business related documents, business plan and certified financial documents need to be submitted. ;Loan Documentation ;Offer Letter;-,;-,;-… Accepted copy of sanction letter (Offer Letter) of the Bank ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_52_74','text':"Security Documents;-,;-,;-… ;Registration of Vehicle in the Bank’s name ;Promissory Note ;Internal Loan Deed. ;Consent Deed. ;Registered Mortgage Deed over Land or Land & Building, as applicable ;Cross collateral deed, as applicable. ;Re-mortgage deed, as applicable. ;Personal/Joint Guarantee /Cross Guarantee / Corporate Guarantee, as applicable. ;Other security documents stated in credit approval terms;-,;-,;-… ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_52_77','text':"Valuation related Documents;-,;-,;-… Valuation report of vehicle from the authorized vehicle dealer of particular vehicle or value assessor of the Bank (in case of refinancing). ;Insurance related Documents;-,;-,;-… (i) Original of Insurance Policy endorsed in Bank’s favor and all endorsements including renewal of policy, (ii)Insurance premium paid receipt. ;Other Documents;-,;-,;-… Tax/V.  A.  T.  Bill of the vehicle (in case of new vehicle). ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_52_82','text':"Recovery Process ;Forthcoming dues to be advised to the customer a one week before the due date in advance. ;A follow up to be made after 15 days of due date if not paid. ;Constant follow up to be made to the customer for realization of uncollected amount. ;In case of delinquency resulting from non-collection of dues, relevant circulars in regard to problem credit management has to be referred and complied accordingly. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_52_87','text':"Other terms and Conditions ;In each case, the Bank reserves the right of refusal without explaining the reason whatsoever. ;Each account need not be reviewed annually. However, in case of delinquency in an account >3 months, CSR regarding recovery action or account strategy needs to be formulated accordingly. ;Charge over the vehicle should be released to the applicant upon full repayment of the dues (principal + interest and other charges), however third party transfers are prohibited. ;Expenses incurred during the process of recovery that is cost to take over the vehicle in bank’s possession and related expenses to be recovered from the customer. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_52_93','text':"Service Procedure ;Submission of duly filled application along with the required supporting documents. ;Personal interview by the Bank official. ;Validate relevant K. Y. C. of the customer/ group vide existing checking account or the one that is to be opened with all documents in place. ;Carry out site inspection of the proposed collateral and the vehicle (for re-financing) for it to be in acceptable condition. Inspection report as well as pictures of the collateral/vehicle must accompany the approval document. ;Processing and submission of credit proposal for approval. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_52_99','text':"After approval of loan, the Bank issues an offer letter to the applicant ;Upon receiving confirmation to the offer letter from applicant, the Bank recover the applicable processing fees and initiate the security documentation process. ;Upon completion of entire internal security documentation and realization of processing fees and other relevant charges, a delivery order (DO) with a validity not exceeding one month from the date of issuance may be issued ;Registration of vehicle in the Bank’s name. ;Undertaking monitoring and control functions, as appropriate. ;Execution of Hire Purchase agreement with the client in order transfer the operational liability of the vehicle to the borrower. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_52_101','text':"Service Standard ;Each application should be processed within 3 working days from the date of receipt of all necessary documents. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_53_4','text':"Type of Loan ;Medium Term loan ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_53_6','text':"Purpose ;To meet personal financial obligations of the borrower. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_53_8','text':"Tenure ;Maximum for a period of 10 years ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_53_14','text':"Eligibility Criteria ;Salaried individuals ;Self-employed professionals ;Individual with self-business establishments or his/her one house family member ;Individual with business/lease/rental/investment income ;Restriction;-,;-,;-… Individuals as Risk Taker (as per the definition of Nepal Rastra Bank) are not eligible to avail loan under this product paper except loan against government Securities. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_53_18','text':"Other Criteria ;Minimum age of the applicant to be 25 Years not exceeding 65 years ;Equated Monthly Installment (E.  M.  I. ) not to be > 50% of the after tax income/cash flow ;Loan will be secured by collateral provided in the form of registered mortgage over Land / Land & Building or Cash / Near Cash Instruments such as Fixed Deposit, Government Bonds, etc ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_53_21','text':"Loan Amount ;Minimum 2 lacs and maximum 25 lacs ;In case of collateral held as Cash/Near Cash instruments, loan amount to be 90% of the face value. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_53_24','text':"Pricing Structure ;As per pricing structure of the individual banks. Normally slightly higher risk premium are added to the base rate in comparison to other retail loans however, ;Interest rate, charges, fees, commission and penal charges will be as decided by the Bank from time to time being within the N.  R.  B.  directives/guidelines. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_53_26','text':"Disbursement Modality ;Once all the security documentation is complete the whole loan amount would be disbursed directly to the borrower’s current account ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_53_28','text':"Repayment ;Loan will be repaid on E. M. I. within the period of maximum 10 years. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_53_30','text':"Prepayment ;Prepayment may be allowed by the banks in term loans being within the guidelines of N.  R.  B. . ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_53_36','text':"Security ;Promissory Note ;Loan Deed ;Mortgage Deed ;Personal Guarantee ;Mortgages or pledges as applicable ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_53_44','text':"Documentation ;Application to be completed by the applicant. ;Map /photos of the applicant’s residence and proposed collateral ;Photograph and Citizenship of the applicant/Guarantor/s ;Self-declaration regarding the applicant is Risk Taker or not in the Bank’s prescribed format. ;Title deed, four boundary certificate and necessary details of the property being offered as collateral if real estate collateral is proposed. ;Proof of age of applicant/Guarantor Relationship certificate, as applicable ;Income statement or cash flow of the applicant/guarantor ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_53_53','text':"Security Documentation ;Accepted copy of our sanction letter ;Insurance Policy with Bank’s interest noted, as applicable ;Insurance premium paid receipt, as applicable ;Personal guarantee of the guarantor/s, as applicable ;Joint guarantee of guarantors, as applicable ;Registered Mortgage over Land/Land & Building / ;Lien/Pledge over Cash/Near Cash Instruments, as applicable ;Internal Loan Deed ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_53_57','text':"Recovery Process ;Constant follow up to be made in case of delinquency in an account more than 1 month ;In case of delinquency in an account more than 3 months, a reminder letter allowing the borrower 15 days to clear the overdue amount would be sent ;CSR (Credit Strategy Review) regarding recovery action to be raised in case of all non-performing loans and approval to be obtained from the respective C. A.D holders. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_53_61','text':"Other terms and Conditions ;In each case, the bank should reserve the right of refusal without explaining the reason whatsoever. ;Variation in pricing may be allowed subject to compliance of all local rules and requisite approval obtained. ;Each account need not be reviewed annually. However, in case of delinquency in an account more than 3 months, a note regarding recovery action needs to be placed in each loan file. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_53_64','text':"Service Standard ;Each application should be processed within 5 working days from the ;date of receipt of all necessary documents. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_54_7','text':"Type of Loan ;Medium to Long Term Loan with structured repayment plan, payable in E. M. I. basis. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_54_10','text':"Purpose ;To part finance tuition fees and related expenses for ;higher/ technical/ professional education. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_54_12','text':"Tenure ;Maximum 10 years ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_54_16','text':"Eligibility Criteria ;Student for which the facility is sought and the applicants applying for the loan should be Nepali National and qualify bank’s K. Y. C. requirements at all times. ;Should have obtained admission, enrolment confirmation in the college / institute destined to pursue further education. ;Minimum and Maximum age of applicant should be 16 years and 65 years respectively. Application made with co-applicant within proposed age range and with established cash flow may be accepted at banks discretion. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_54_19','text':"Applications made by the individuals other than student and/or the parent (father and/or mother) must involve the student as a co-applicant Le single person made application is allowed only to the extent of the student and/or the parent ;Fixed assets collateral guarantees, sponsorships, cash flow commitments etc. may be accepted only from the applicant and one house family member of the applicant and/or as per N.  R.  B.  directives/circulars ;Applicant could be one house family members of the student, immediate and close relatives both at paternal and maternal side who wish to support/sponsor for his/her study. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_54_21','text':"Eligible Income ;Eligible income of Parents/Grandparents / Maternal Grandparents or Uncle / individual from one house family member/Guarantor/s will quality if any of the following is;-,;-,;-… ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_54_22','text':"a) Salaried individuals ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_54_23','text':"b) Self-employed professionals ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_54_24','text':"c) Self-employed businessmen ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_54_25','text':"d) Individual having identified source of income for example: lease, business, pension etc. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_54_27','text':"Eligible Course ;a) Studies in Nepal ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_54_28','text':"Professional courses;-,;-,;-… Medicine (MBBS, Public Health, Physiotherapy, Pathology, Nursing etc and master degree courses in similar disciplines), Pharmacy, BDS, Engineering, Veterinary, Management, Computer and Technology. Professional Accounting/Finance related courses such as C. A., ICWA and CF.  A.  ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_54_29','text':"Post-Graduation Courses;-,;-,;-… Masters, M. Phil and PhD. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_54_30','text':"b) Studies Abroad ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_54_31','text':"Graduation/Post Graduation level studies related to professional and technical courses ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_54_32','text':"Diploma studies related to professional and technical courses. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_54_33','text':"Certificate Level Courses ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_54_34','text':"Language courses. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_54_35','text':"Training courses such as pilot ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_54_36','text':"Other eligible courses will be as approved by the bank’s competent authority on the recommendation made by designated department that is Retail Bank. Such approvals will be considered as integral part of this product paper. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_54_38','text':"Loan Amount ;Minimum size of each loan to be Nepali Rupees 150,000/- (Nepalese rupees one hundred fifty thousand only), ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_54_39','text':"Maximum size of each loan to be Nepali Rupees 10,000,000 (Nepalese rupees ten million only) under this product paper. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_54_40','text':"The loan amount not to be more than 100% of the Distress Value of Land or Land & Building (as valued by the Bank’s authorized valuator). ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_54_41','text':"Maximum 90% of Face Value of Cash/ Near Cash Instruments such as Fixed Deposit, Government Bonds, etc. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_54_43','text':"Pricing Structure ;Interest rate, charges, fees and commission on the facility will as per bank’s STC being within N.  R.  B. ’s guidelines ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_54_44','text':"Administrative Service Fee is to be deposited at the time of processing of the application, however, it will not be refunded if the applicant fails to take the loan for any other reasons other than the Bank’s refusal of the proposal. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_54_47','text':"Disbursement Modality ;• ;Disbursement to be made upon completion of loan documents. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_54_48','text':"Disbursement to be made during the tuition course period. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_54_50','text':"Yearly living expenses to be disbursed in 2 tranches ;- 50% in first six months and remaining 50% after six months’ period. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_54_52','text':"Repayment ;Equated Monthly Installments (E.  M.  I. ) over a period of 10 years. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_54_53','text':"A moratorium of maximum 12 (twelve) months may be provided from the date of first drawdown, however interest will be charged during the period. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_54_58','text':"Prepayment ;Prepayments of the loan shall be allowed under following conditions;-,;-,;-… ;Any amount above Nepali Rupees 50,000/- except in case of final settlement of loan in full. ;The amount prepaid/repaid shall not be available for further disbursal / withdrawal. ;Commitment Fee shall be applied as per the Standard Tariff of Charges of the Bank being within the N.  R.  B.  guidelines. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_54_61','text':"Upon prepayment, E. M. I. schedule may be re-aligned ;Pre-settlement/cancellation of loan during the educational course tenure is normally restricted however, on special case it may be allowed with specific approval. ;In case of pre-settlement/cancellation of loan, the bank shall report the concerned education institution or other concerned parties (if required) at its sole discretion ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_54_64','text':"Security ;Land or Land & Building and/or Cash or Near Cash Security such as Fixed Deposit, Government Security. ;Security must be in the name of the applicant or one house family member of the applicant. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_54_71','text':"Documentation ;Loan Application form duly filled by the applicant’s and co-signed by the student as appropriate. ;Copy of academic certificates of the student. ;Offer letter of admission from the institution. ;Detailed address (with diagram) of the residence of the applicants, guarantors, sponsor/s and student ;Photograph, Citizenship and other K. Y. C. required documents of all involved individuals ;Net worth statement of the applicant/sponsor/guarantor/ student, as applicable. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_54_76','text':"Details of the security being offered as collateral. ;Title Deed, four boundary certificate, trace map, revenue receipt of land or land and building offered as collateral. In case of loan secured against building within a Municipality, documents certifying fulfilment of required standards set by the competent authority such as approved drawing (Naksapass), approval from concerned authorities, building construction completion certificate should be obtained. ;Income statement or cash flow details of the applicant/ sponsor/guarantor / student (where applicable);-,;-,;-… ;a) In case of salaried Individuals ;Certification of salary or salary statement from the employing organization/company ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_54_86','text':"Bank statements, as applicable. ;b) in case of self-employed professionals ;Registration document from concerned professional association/council. ;Detail of income source/ profession. ;Bank Statement, as applicable. ;c) in case of self-employed businessman ;Business Registration Document ;Income Tax Certificate. ;Latest Audited Financial Statements ;Bank Statement, as applicable. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_54_91','text':"d) In case of other sources ;Latest lease payment receipt or agreements, title deed of property, as applicable Details of other lease income. ;Pension slip, interest received statement etc ;Bank statements, as applicable. Loan Documentation ;Offer Letter;-,;-,;-… Accepted copy of sanction letter (Offer Letter) of the Bank ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_54_99','text':"Security Documents ;Internal Loan Deed. ;Registered Mortgage Deed over Land or Land & Building, as applicable. ;Lien/Pledge over cash/near cash security such as Fixed Deposit, Government Security, as applicable ;Letter of Undertaking in case of cash / near cash security. ;Commitment letter from the FD owner, where applicable. ;Rokka Letter in case of government security. ;Blank endorsement in case of government security. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_54_106','text':"Personal/Joint Guarantee of the parents/guarantor/ Collateral owner. ;Consent (Manjurinaama) of spouse of collateral owner. ;Other security documents stated in credit approval terms. ;Valuation related Documents;-,;-,;-… Valuation report of the property offered as collateral. Approved valuator of the Bank shall carry out the valuation as per the standard terms of reference of the Bank ;Insurance related Documents;-,;-,;-… ;Original of Insurance Policy endorsed in Bank’s favour and all endorsements including renewal of policy covering at least against the risk of fire and earthquake. ;Insurance premium paid receipt. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_54_111','text':"Recovery Process ;In case of delinquency in an account for more than 1 month, a follow up letter would be sent to the student in his/her last known address (abroad) along with the applicant/ sponsor/ guarantors registered address in Nepal. ;In case of delinquency in an account remained for more than 3 months, a reminder letter asking the borrower / sponsor/ guarantor to clear off the overdue amount by 15 days from the date of the letter to be sent. ;CSR (Credit Strategy Review) regarding recovery ;action to be raised in case of all non-performing loans. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_54_117','text':"Other terms and Conditions ;In each case, the Bank should reserve the right of refusal without explaining the reason whatsoever. ;Variation in pricing may be allowed subject to compliance of all local rules and requisite approval obtained. ;•Each account need not be reviewed annually. However, in case of delinquency in an account for more than 3 consecutive months, CSR regarding recovery action needs to be placed in each folder ;•Charge over assets should be released to the applicant upon full repayment of the dues (principal + interest) ;however, third party transfers are prohibited. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_54_122','text':"Service Procedure ;Submission of duly filled application along with the required supporting documents. ;•Personal interview by the Bank official ;•Conduct on-site inspection of the proposed collateral along with the bank’s authorized valuator and obtain preliminary property valuation report along with property related relevant documents. ;•Processing and submission of credit proposal for approval. The proposal to accompany required basic documents and fulfil all relevant terms and conditions. Processing fees to be collected upfront ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_54_128','text':"After approval of loan, the Bank issues an offer letter to the applicant ;Upon receiving confirmation to the offer letter from applicant, the Bank to initiate final valuation of proposed property through Bank’s approved valuator and security documentation process. ;Mortgage over property being part of the collateral, as applicable ;Disbursal should be made on demand not exceeding the eligible value cost based on presented valid documents ;Undertaking monitoring and control functions, as ;appropriate. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_54_130','text':"Service Standard ;Each application should be processed within 4 (four) working days from the date of receipt of all necessary documents ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_55_9','text':"Purpose ;For financing fixed and current assets that will support business operation ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_55_11','text':"Tenure ;Minimum 2 years, maximum 6 years ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_55_17','text':"Eligibility Criteria ;The applicant should be either of the following;-,;-,;-… ;Sole Proprietorship Firm. ;Private Limited Firm having single owner. In case of more than single owners, the owners to be from immediate family members only. ;Individuals who possess academic qualifications in technical ;profession for example: Medical Doctors, Engineers, Chartered Accountants, etc. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_55_18','text':"Proprietor/key person of the business should have at least 2 years’ experience in the related business field. For professionals, the experience may not be required. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_55_19','text':"There should not be any business credit line/s of the borrower with other financial institutions . ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_55_21','text':"Basic Criteria ;Minimum age of the proprietor/owner to be 25 Years. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_55_22','text':"Maximum age of the proprietor/owner to be 65 Years. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_55_23','text':"E. M. I. not to be more than 70% of cash flow (Actual/Projected). ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_55_24','text':"Loan to be secured by registered mortgage over real estate (land and/or land & building) and coverage to be at least 125% in Distress Value terms. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_55_31','text':"Loan Amount ;Minimum loan size to be Nepali Rupees 200,000/- ;Maximum loan size to be Nepali Rupees 2,500,000/- under this product paper. However the total aggregated exposure to one counterpart cannot exceed an absolute threshold of Nepali Rupees 10 Million. ;Note;-,;-,;-… ;Aggregated exposure means amount of all forms of credit exposures availed from the Bank. ;Counterpart refers to one or group of borrowers defined by the N.  R.  B.  Directives as a single borrower. ;Loan amount should not exceed 75% of the cost of fixed assets and/or current assets. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_55_33','text':"Pricing Structure ;Interest rate, charges, fees, commission and penal charges will be as decided by the Bank from time to time. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_55_42','text':"Disbursement Modality ;Disbursement to be made upon completion of loan documents based on value of Current Assets/Fixed Assets being financed. ;In case of Current Assets;-,;-,;-… ;Disbursal not to exceed 75% of the current assets including the inventory to be purchased. ;Quotation/invoice to be obtained. ;3. In case of Fixed Assets;-,;-,;-… ;Disbursal not to exceed 75% of the cost in case of complete purchase. ;Quotation/invoice to be obtained. ;In case of construction / renovation of go down / storage facilities / work station, verification to be made through physical inspection prior disbursal in full / part. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_55_45','text':"Repayment ;Loan will be repaid on E.  M.  I. . ;Principal moratorium (inclusive of the loan tenure) may be allowed depending upon the business / project being financed. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_55_47','text':"Prepayment ;Prepayments are allowed without any penalty charges ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_55_50','text':"Security ;Land or Land & Building and/or Cash or Near Cash Collateral (Deposit with the Bank, Government Bonds only). ;General / specific charge over the project under finance (as applicable). ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_55_56','text':"Documentation ;Loan Application in the prescribed format ;Photograph and copy of citizenship of the proprietor / directors / guarantor ;Map of the applicant’s/director’s/guarantor’s residence and business site ;Renewed Firm/Company registration certificate. ;Renewed Income Tax Certificate, PAN and latest tax paid receipt. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_55_62','text':"Copy of M. O. A. and A.O.A and board minute permitting bank borrowing in case of Private Limited. ;Details of property being offered as collateral. ;Proof of estimated costs of the asset/s that is to be financed, as applicable. ;Historical/projected financial statements as applicable. ;Proof of the income from other sources, where applicable. ;Document/statement evidencing experience of the Owner/ Guarantor ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_55_69','text':"Loan Documentation ;Offer Letter;-,;-,;-… Accepted copy of sanction letter (Offer Letter) ;Security Documents o Internal Loan Deed. ;Registered Mortgage Deed over Land & Building, as applicable. ;Lien / Pledge over cash or near cash security, as applicable. ;Hypothecation charge over the current assets, as applicable. ;Hypothecation charge over plant & machinery, as applicable. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_55_74','text':"Personal / Joint Guarantee/Cross Guarantee, as applicable. ;Valuation related Documents;-,;-,;-… Valuation report of land & building offered as collateral. The approved valuator of the Bank will value the real estate as per the standard terms of reference of the Bank. ;Insurance related Documents ;Insurance Policy endorsed in Bank’s name/Bank’s charge, in case of registered mortgaged over building or hypothecation charge over machinery/current assets (as applicable). ;Insurance premium paid receipt. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_55_77','text':"Recovery Process ;Constant follow up to be made in case of delinquency in an account is more than 1 month. ;In case of delinquency in an account is more than 3 months, a reminder letter allowing the borrower 35 days to clear the overdue amount ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_55_79','text':"CSR (Credit Strategy Review) regarding recovery action to be raised in case of all non-performing loans. ;Relationship would be handed over to the recovery unit of the bank for necessary action against the borrower. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_55_83','text':"Credit Monitoring ;Disbursal of credit line within the disbursal norms where by ratio to debt and equity is adequately maintained at all times. ;Inspection to be carried out within 3 months of each disbursal. However, in case of overdue of interest and / or principal more than 2 months, inspection report to be filed for reason/s of delay in repayment and time frame by which the overdue amount will be settled. ;Annual inspection to the unit/firm should be conducted. Details of the site inspection should be recorded in prescribed format along with pictures of the fixed/current assets being financed. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_55_88','text':"Service Procedure ;Submission of application along with the required supporting documents. ;Personal Interview by the bank official. ;Processing and submission of credit proposal for approval. ;Provided the loan application is accepted, valuation to be done by Bank’s approved valuator. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_55_92','text':"After approval of the loan, the Bank issues an offer letter to the applicant. ;The applicant after adding his/her confirmation to the offer letter, the Bank initiates the process of mortgage over tangible assets being part of the collateral. ;Checking and verification of all the security, insurance and valuation documents. ;Implementing the credit lines as approved. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_55_94','text':"Service Standard ;Each application should be processed within 5 working days from the date of receipt of all necessary documents and inform the customer regarding acceptance or rejection of the proposal. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_57_37','text':"S.No. ;Standalone Model (Branch Level Processing) ;Centralised Model ;(Retail Loan Processing Hubs/Centres) ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_57_40','text':"1. ;Better Understanding of the customer requirements. ;Based on documents only. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_57_43','text':"2. ;No standardised approach ;Standardised approach. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_57_46','text':"3. ;Retail Loans are only one part of the faster multiple activities. ;Exclusive activity and hence will be more and professional in approach. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_57_49','text':"4. ;Difference in quality of appraisal based on the branch and its personnel. ;Quality will be uniform as the activity is exclusive. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_57_52','text':"5. ;Processing time may differ based on the priorities of the branches and importance of the customers/proposals. ;Processing time will be uniform and fixed Turn Around Time (TAT) for different retail loans. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_57_55','text':"6. ;Compliance of appraisal norms may be based on the customer profile. ;Uniform and impersonal appraisal standards. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_57_59','text':"7. ;Documentation standards may not be ;uniform. ;Professional documentation standards. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_57_60','text':"The above details are only illustrative and not exhaustive. To sum up, RLPCs definitely have an edge with regard to processing of retail loans as compared to processing at branches. But as said above, branches will understand the customers’ requirements on a personal basis as against the mechanical approach of RLPCs. But the introduction of RLPCs by banks has definitely helped banks to improve the quality appraisal and reduce the documentation gaps as compared to branch level appraisal. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_57_61','text':"Let Us Sum Up ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_57_62','text':"In the retail asset side, the important products offered by banks are Home Loans, Educational Loans, Personal Loans and other retail loans developed for specific customer segments. Each loan is designed for a specific purpose and need and structured in such a way that the needs and requirements of different customers are taken care of. Banks process and sanction retail loans ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_57_63','text':"in two different ways. They sanction retail loans on a standalone basis (through the branches) or through a centralised model (through retail loan processing hubs/centres). Each model has its own advantages as well as disadvantages. In the branch model, personal touch is more, in the centralised model, more professional approach is followed. The  of RLPCs has definitely helped banks to improve the quality of appraisal and also has reduced the gaps and deficiencies in the documentation side. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_57_64','text':"Keywords ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_57_65','text':"Retail Loans; Home Loans; Auto Loans; Personal Loans; Educational Loans; Retail Loan Processing Centres ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_60_2','text':"What is a credit card? A credit card is a thin plastic card, usually 3–1/8 inches by 2–1/8 inches in size that contains identification information such as a signature or picture, and authorizes the person named on it to charge purchases or services to his account – charges for which he will be billed periodically. The information on the card can be read by ATMs, Point Of Sales (PoS) Terminals at different establishments like Textile Stores, Super Markets, Jewellery Showrooms, Book Shops, Restaurants, etc. Before we go into the details of the end to end process cycle of the issue, use and management of credit cards, let us have a look into the ."}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_60_58','text':"Nabil VISA Domestic Credit ;Card ;SCB VISA Classic Credit ;Card ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_60_61','text':"Acceptance ;Nepal and India ;Nepal and India ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_60_65','text':"Tap and Pay ;Contactless, doesn’t require ;PIN verification ;- ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_60_70','text':"Flexibility of repayment ;Flexible bill payment options of 10% to 100% of your ;outstanding ;Flexible bill payment options of 2% to 100% of ;your outstanding ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_60_75','text':"Convenience ;Online/offline purchase ;through wide VISA Network ;Online through wide VISA ;Network ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_60_78','text':"Transaction Alert ;With instant SMS and email ;With instant SMS and email ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_60_82','text':"Security ;Secure Chip card with go e-secure ;digital security system ;Secure Chip Card ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_60_86','text':"PIN generation ;Eco friendly Green PIN ;Green PIN which can be ;generated from ATM ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_60_89','text':"Validity ;4 years ;3 years ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_60_94','text':"Statement ;e-Statement via smart app and ;email ;e-Statement via smart app ;and email ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_60_99','text':"(source;-,;-,;-… ;https://www.sc.com/np/credit-cards/visa-classic/ ;and ;https://www.nabilbank.com/ ;services-payments/services/credit-card/nabil-visa-domestic-credit-card ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_60_167','text':"Interest Free Period does not apply for Cash Advances and Revolving Balances."}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_60_168','text':"Annualised Percentage Rate (A. P.R):"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_60_169','text':"Interest will be charged for the unpaid balances as on the due date and also subsequent purchases. The interest rate was expressed as a monthly percentage rate previously to reduce the impact of high rates when calculated on an annualized basis. But regulatory prescription had resulted in credit card issuers to clearly mention the interest rate on an annualised percentage rate. The monthly interest is annualized to arrive at the Annualised Percentage Rate (A. P.R). As an illustration, let us see the A. P. R. charges by a card issuing bank for different types of transactions."}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_60_170','text':"Monthly retail interest of 3.1% p.m. is annualised to arrive at an A. P. R. of 37.20%"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_60_171','text':"Cash Transactions will attract an interest rate of 3.49% and A. P. R. of 41.88%."}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_60_172','text':"The interest rate for retail transactions is variable and will vary between 2.49% p.m. (A. P. R. of 29.88%) and 3.49% p.m. (A. P. R. of 41.88%)."}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_60_179','text':"S. No. ;Type of facility/Penalty ;Charges ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_60_182','text':"1. ;Cash Advance Transaction Fee ;2% per month + Nepali Rupees 100 (vary from bank to bank) ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_60_185','text':"2. ;Card Replacement (lost/stolen/ re-issue/ any other) ;NPR 750/- (vary from bank to bank) ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_60_188','text':"3. ;Overdue Penalty/Late Payment Fee ;24% p.a. of Total Amount Due and Rupees 300 per instance (vary from bank to bank) ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_60_191','text':"4. ;Over Limit Penalty ;NPR 500/- (vary from bank to bank) ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_60_192','text':"The charges are structured high to prompt repayment in time and operate within limits with sufficient balance in accounts to honour repayment cheques. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_60_193','text':"The above discussions on credit cards and their different dimensions throw open lot of important revelations about credit cards. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_60_194','text':"Credit Cards are customer friendly initiatives empowering them with financial limits to use it for different purposes including cash withdrawals. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_60_195','text':"But credit cards if not used judiciously will result in a debt trap on account of high financial charges and interest charges. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_60_196','text':"Credit Cards Receivables are unsecured advances for banks and hence higher pricing for card receivables. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_60_197','text':"Profitability from credit card operations is quite high due to higher interest charges but at the same time, the defaults/delinquencies will also be on the higher side. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_60_198','text':"Credit card usage should be strictly as per the terms of the card and any deviation will attract heavy charges. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_63_34','text':"S.No. ;Credit Cards ;Debit Cards ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_63_37','text':"1. ;Different Types of Credit Cards are offered by different banks. ;All banks offer a standard type of Debit Card either with Visa or Master Card. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_63_40','text':"2. ;Card Limit varies with individuals. ;No limit prescribed as drawing is from the existing balance in the account. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_63_43','text':"3. ;Allows purchases at one point and payment to be made subsequently. ;Purchase and payment are happening at the same time. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_63_46','text':"4. ;Free Credit Period is allowed. ;Not applicable as payment is instantaneous. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_63_49','text':"5. ;Payment can be made in E.  M.  I. s converting the dues as a loan. ;Direct debit from the account at the point purchase. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_63_52','text':"6. ;Interest is charged for unpaid and carried over balances. ;Not applicable as payment is instant. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_63_55','text':"7. ;Various Charges/Penalties are levied for facilities and defaults. ;No penalty or charge of any nature. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_63_58','text':"8. ;Specific Cash Withdrawal Limits are set within the card limits. ;The limits can be set as per customers’ requirements. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_63_61','text':"9. ;Default Risk is high. ;No Default Risk. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_63_64','text':"10. ;Assumes the character of an Asset;-,;-,;-… when the card is used it becomes a Receivable. an Asset account for the bank. ;Debit Card is only an operative instrument of a Liability Account. (Savings Accounts) ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_63_65','text':"The above mentioned items are some of the visible differences between Credit Cards and Debit Cards. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_65_2','text':"A Contactless card is a faster way to pay with a credit or debit card for purchases and payments below Nepali Rupees 5,000/- at participating stores. Instead of dipping (or swiping) the card at the billing counter, simply wave or tap the card on the contactless terminal and pay without entering a PIN. These cards work on Near-Field Communication (NFC) technology, which employs radio transmission to ascertain contact when the cards are tapped or waved near a terminal. These enable customers to make payments by waving or tapping the cards instead of swiping them. The speed at which the transaction can be carried out is almost double that of traditional cards."}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_65_3','text':"The key advantage is that; this card takes less time for completion of the transaction. The card need not leave the customer’s hand while in operation which enhances the level of security. Contactless technology uses secure encryption (the same as CHIP and PIN) so it can be confidently used. The maximum transaction value for a contactless transaction is capped at Nepali Rupees 5,000/- which further limits any possible loss. Furthermore, the card holder is protected in case of loss or theft of the card, provided the same is reported to the issuing bank on time."}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_65_4','text':"In Nepal, Nabil Bank was the first bank to launch such contactless cards under NFC technology in 2019 and many other banks follow to launch such card, like; Mega Bank, Bank of Kathmandu, Machhapuchhre and many other banks launched contactless card in Nepalese payment system."}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_65_6','text':"We have seen what a credit card is, how it facilitates the credit function and what constitutes the credit card transaction cycle. We also saw a brief history of the evolution of the credit card industry along with the role of important players like the network sponsors such as Visa, Master Card, SCTN, NEPS, NPN, banks, etc. In addition to credit cards, the chapter provided an overview of various other types of cards like Debit Cards, Contactless Cards, Co-branded Cards, Pre-paid Cards, etc."}]},
