{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_157_103','text':"If you wish to calculate FVF of Re. 1 at 12% from 1 to 6 years by using simple calculator, do following. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_157_106','text':"(1) Press 1.12 (2) press multiplication sign ;that is ;X twice (press x, press x) (3) you get 1.12. Thus 1.12. is FVF for 1 year term. (4) for FVF for year 2, just press equal sign (=), you get ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_157_107','text':"1.25 (5) for FVF for year3, just press equal sign (=), you get 1.40 (6) for FVF for year 4, just press equal sign (=), you get 1.57 (7) for FVF for year 5, just press equal sign (=), you get 1.76 (8) for FVF for year 6, just press equal sign (=), you get 1.97. This way, you can find FVF of at any rate of interest for any term. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_157_108','text':"Let us work out one example. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_157_112','text':"If Nepali Rupees 1,00,000 is invested for a period of 6 years at interest at 11% p.a. find the maturity sum ;that is, ;future value ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_157_113','text':"Future value = PV × future value factor FV = 1,00,000 × 1.87 = 1,87,000 ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_157_114','text':"Solving problem through MS EXCEL program. The in-built function of FV in excel is —— FV (RATE, NPE. R., PV, TYPE) ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_157_115','text':"FV = Future value, RATE = rate of interest, NPE. R. = Total number of periods, PV = present value. PMT and TYPE are included to handle annuities (a series of payments equally spaced over a period of time).TYPE is for indicating whether the cash flow occurs at the beginning ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_157_116','text':"(1) or at the end (0) of the period. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_157_119','text':"If Nepali Rupees 1,00,000 is invested for a period of 6 years at interest at 11% p.a. find the future value at the end of the period. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_157_120','text':"Enter;-,;-,;-… FV (0.11,6,0 – 1,00,000, 0) [Please do not forget to put minus sign (–) before PV] The result is Nepali Rupees 1,87,041. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_157_121','text':"Future value of annuities ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_157_122','text':"Annuities are essentially series of fixed payments required from you or paid to you at a specified frequency over the course of a fixed period of time. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_157_123','text':"Ordinary Annuity ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_157_124','text':";-,;-,;-… Payments are made/received at the end of each period. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_157_125','text':"Annuity Due ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_157_126','text':";-,;-,;-… Payments are made/received at the beginning of each period. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_157_139','text':"= Nepali Rupees 1000*5.53* 1.05"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_157_157','text':"1 ;1.00 ;1.00 ;1.00 ;1.00 ;1.00 ;1.00 ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_157_164','text':"2 ;2.070 ;2.080 ;2.090 ;2.100 ;2.110 ;2.120 ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_157_171','text':"3 ;3.215 ;3.246 ;3.278 ;3.310 ;3.342 ;3.374 ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_157_178','text':"4 ;4.440 ;4.506 ;4.573 ;4.641 ;4.710 ;4.779 ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_157_185','text':"5 ;5.751 ;5.867 ;5.985 ;6.105 ;6.228 ;6.353 ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_157_192','text':"6 ;7.153 ;7.336 ;7.523 ;7.716 ;7.913 ;8.115 ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_157_194','text':"If Ms. Anusaya is paying home loan instalment at Nepali Rupees 12,000 per year for a period of 6 years how much she paid till the end of the loan period (What is the future value of an annuity of Nepali Rupees 10,000 p.a. at 11%for a period of 6 years). ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_157_196','text':"By using the annuity table above, find CVA factor for 6 years at 11% and multiply by Nepali Rupees 10,000.CVA for 6 years @ 11% = 7.913 ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_157_197','text':"Annuity = Nepali Rupees 10,000 ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_157_198','text':"So Future value of annuity = 7.913 × 10,000 = Nepali Rupees 79,130 ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_157_199','text':"Present Value ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_157_200','text':"Present value is nothing but the reverse of future value. For finding out present value (PV), we must use discounting formula which is given below;-,;-,;-… ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_157_201','text':"{PV\  = \ FV\  \div \ (1\  + \ r)}^{n} ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_157_202','text':"Where PV means present value, 1 means one rupee, r means rate of interest and n means period or term and FV means future value. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_157_204','text':"If Nepali Rupees 1,61,000 is the maturity value(future value) of investment, invested for a period of 5 years at interest at 10% p.a. find the amount invested (present value). ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_157_205','text':"Solution;-,;-,;-… ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_157_206','text':"The formula for finding PV is——- ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_157_207','text':"PV ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_157_209','text':"= ;\frac{\mathbf{FV}}{\mathbf{(1\  + \ r)}^{\mathbf{n}}} ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_157_211','text':"= 161000/(1 + 0.10) ;5 ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_157_212','text':"= 161000/(1.61) ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_157_213','text':"= 161000(1.61) ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_157_214','text':"= 100000 ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_157_215','text':"So, the present value will be Nepali Rupees 1,00,000 ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_157_216','text':"The same value can be calculated by using present value table. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_157_217','text':"Present Value = FV × Present Value Factor ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_157_218','text':"Present Value Factors (PVF) of Nepali Rupees 1 at different rates of interest are given below for information ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_157_232','text':"1 ;0.93 ;0.93 ;0.92 ;0.91 ;0.90 ;0.89 ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_157_239','text':"2 ;0.87 ;0.86 ;0.84 ;0.83 ;0.81 ;0.80 ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_157_246','text':"3 ;0.81 ;0.79 ;0.77 ;0.75 ;0.73 ;0.71 ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_157_253','text':"4 ;0.76 ;0.74 ;0.71 ;0.68 ;0.66 ;0.63 ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_157_260','text':"5 ;0.71 ;0.68 ;0.65 ;0.62 ;0.59 ;0.57 ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_157_267','text':"6 ;0.66 ;0.63 ;0.60 ;0.56 ;0.53 ;0.51 ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_157_268','text':"Solving Present Value problems with the use of Excel Program. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_157_269','text':"The in-built function of PV in excel is— PV (RATE, NPE. R., FV, TYPE) ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_157_270','text':"PV = Present value, RATE = rate of interest, NPE. R. = Total number of periods FV = Future value. TYPE is for indicating whether the cash flow occurs at the beginning (1) or at the end (0) of the period. ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_157_272','text':"Example ;-,;-,;-… ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_157_273','text':"If the maturity value of an amount invested for a period of 6 years at interest at 11% p.a. is Nepali Rupees 1,87,041 find the amount invested at the beginning (find present value). ;"}]},
{'title':'rb', 'content':[{'fname':'RB_h_157_274','text':"Enter;-,;-,;-… PV(11%, 6, 0, 187041,0) [Please do not forget to put minus sign (–) before FV]The result is Nepali Rupees 1,00,000. ;"}]},
